HOUSE BILL 1570
P3 6lr3226
By: Delegate Young
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Government, Labor, and Elections
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Government – Governmental Procedures – Development and Review of
3 Standards
4 FOR the purpose of establishing certain requirements for standards developed by units of
5 State government; requiring the periodic review of standards adopted by units of
6 State government; and generally relating to standards developed by units of State
7 government.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – State Government
10 Section 10–1703
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – State Government
16 10–1703.
17 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
18 INDICATED.
19 (2) “DECISION–SUPPORT ALGORITHM” MEANS A COMPUTER
20 PROGRAM USED BY A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT TO IMPROVE DECISION MAKING
21 THAT IS EVALUATED BY A TECHNICAL EXPERT BEFORE BEING USED.
22 (3) “STANDARDS” MEANS OPERATIONAL, TECHNICAL, OR
23 PROCEDURAL BENCHMARKS USED TO GUIDE IMPLEMENTATION PROCESSES.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1570*

2 HOUSE BILL 1570
1 (B) IN DEVELOPING STANDARDS, A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT SHALL:
2 (1) RELY ONLY ON FEASIBLE, TRANSPARENT, AND REPRODUCIBLE
3 DATA;
4 (2) INCORPORATE FIRST–HAND KNOWLEDGE, INCLUDING BEST
5 PRACTICES AND REAL–WORLD EXPERIENCES;
6 (3) SEEK CONSENSUS AMONG STAKEHOLDERS;
7 (4) RESOLVE DISPUTES THROUGH INDEPENDENT THIRD–PARTY
8 TECHNICAL REVIEW USING RECOGNIZED RESEARCH AND EXPERTISE AND
9 REFERENCE TO RECOGNIZED INTERNATIONAL STANDARDS;
10 (5) AVOID RELYING ON TECHNICAL EXPERTS FOUND TO BE BIASED,
11 AS DETERMINED BY INDEPENDENT REVIEWS;
12 (6) TAKE INTO ACCOUNT:
13 (I) TRANSFORMATIVE LARGE–SCALE ECONOMIC EFFICIENCY;
14 (II) SCIENTIFIC STANDARDS;
15 (III) CULTURAL PRACTICES;
16 (IV) COMPARATIVE ADVANTAGES; AND
17 (V) STRUCTURED INPUT FROM MULTIDISCIPLINARY EXPERTS;
18 AND
19 (7) UTILIZE A DECISION–SUPPORT ALGORITHM.
20 (C) ANY INITIAL STANDARDS ADOPTED BY A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT
21 SHALL:
22 (1) BE BASED ON EXISTING CODES AND REGULATIONS, UNLESS
23 OTHERWISE SPECIFIED;
24 (2) CONFIRM EXISTING PRACTICES AND STANDARDS; AND
25 (3) CLEARLY DEFINE GOALS, RISKS, AND METHODS.

HOUSE BILL 1570 3
1 (D) ANY STANDARDS ADOPTED BY A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT SHALL
2 BE REVIEWED PERIODICALLY USING:
3 (1) CURRENT TECHNOLOGICAL BEST PRACTICES; AND
4 (2) INDEPENDENT PEER INPUT.
5 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
6 October 1, 2026.

